        {
          "@type": "Review",
          "itemReviewed": {
            "@type": "School",
            "name": "DSK School - Dhiree Village,Dhayari"
          },
          "author": {
            "@type": "Person",
            "name": "Kitty Cat"
          },
          "datePublished": "2022-01-24",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "I studied in this school for 9 years. I was a 2017 pass out student. According to what I've experienced,the teaching staff was extremely rude and demotivating. Some teachers used to beat students for the most minor mistakes. As I grew older the teaching staff became even worse. Some teachers used to pay attention to only few (Favorite) students in the class. My own experience is that I was constantly targeted by few teachers and was made to sit on the last benches despite having a good academic record. I was good at athletics and sports but was never allowed to participate in school competitions or Karandak's because obviously I wasn't their 'favorite' kid. The school needs to change most of their staff and stop picking on the students who are shy or who lack confidence. I believe school years are very essential and those are the times when schools are supposed to help students built up confidence and speaking skills. Sadly, my school failed to do that but it made me stronger. Apart from that, the infrastructure is good, the school has a huge playground and the surrounding nature is great.",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
        }
